==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maternity
<hw>Ma*ter"ni*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>maternit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, LL. <ets>maternitas</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being a mother; motherhood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The character of a mother; maternal quality;
motherliness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The maternity ward; the maternity department of a
hospital.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>maternity</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: maternity
<hw>ma*ter"ni*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to childbirth or the period during which a woman is pregnant;
<as>as, <ex>maternity</ex> care; a <ex>maternity</ex>
hospital</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>For use during pregnancy; <as>as, a
<ex>maternity</ex> outfit</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>maternity ward</ent>⟦br⟧
